President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the state of Idaho due to flooding from March 29 to June 15, 2017. Federal assistance will be provided to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts. Federal funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Timothy B. Manner has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.